         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#chaniotisrrrs2016">
            <p><note>A</note>: The sarcophagus and the platform and the place [? -- and the - ] on which it stands, belong to Marcus Aurelius Zenon, son of Zenon, son of Papos, son of Severus, 
               in which he will be buried himself and his sons. No other person shall have authorisation to bury someone or to remove someone of the aforementioned, 
               for (otherwise) he shall pay to the professional association of the leather-workers
               3500 <foreign>denarii</foreign>, one-third of which shall belong to the <foreign>vindicator</foreign>.
               <note>B</note>: Of Elpidios.</p>
         </div>
